President Trump announced his nomination of Kirstjen Nielsen as the next Secretary of Homeland Security. He praised Nielsen's dedication to the safety and security of the country and highlighted her previous experience in the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) as well as her current role as Principal Deputy Chief of Staff at the White House. Trump called on the Senate to confirm Nielsen quickly, emphasizing the urgent need for strong leadership at DHS. Nielsen expressed her gratitude for the nomination and pledged to work every day to protect and secure the homeland. She also acknowledged the recent natural disasters and the ongoing recovery efforts, promising to remain fully engaged in the rebuilding process. Nielsen thanked General John Kelly for his leadership and expressed her commitment to continuing his work at DHS.